  <static seed="2431" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Exponents/exponentsMultiplication23.pg">
    <statement><p>Use the properties of exponents to simplify the expression.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(5x\right)^2}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="12" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>25x^{2}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>We <em>multiply</em> the exponents and apply the rule <m>(ab)^m=a^m\cdot b^m</m> as follows: <me>\begin{aligned}
           \left(5x\right)^{2}\amp =(5)^{2}x^{2}\\
                             \amp =25x^{2}
       \end{aligned}</me></p>
</solution>
